snippet: The bride is pursuing a doctorate in communications; the bridegroom is a lawyer.
lead_paragraph: Kara Maureen Garrity, a daughter of Rosemary A. Garrity and James J. Garrity of Spring House, Pa., was married Saturday to Paul Jude Liebeskind, the son of Lenore F. Liebeskind and Alan M. Liebeskind of Dumont, N.J. The Rev. Otto H. Hentz, a Roman Catholic priest, performed the ceremony at the Dahlgren Chapel on Georgetown's campus in Washington. The couple, both 26, met at Georgetown, from which they graduated, she cum laude and he magna cum laude.
